  Automation Framework
-----------------------
is used to organize automation project files/folders in structured manner.

Objectives
1)Re-usability   2)Maintainability   3)Readability 

Types of Frameworks
--------------------
1) Built-in
		Ex: testng,jnuit,cucumber(bdd testing),robot(python) etc.
2)Customized(user defined)
		Ex: modular framework,data driver,keywork driven,hybrid driven etc.
		
Phases/Stages
-------------
1)Analysing AUT
	-Number of pages
	-Type of elements/how
	-what to automate/what we cannot automate  Ex:(100 test cases--90 automatable, 10 manually tested)100%Automation
---->Tests we cannot automate -->Manually(verify colors,font size/style,captchas,graphs,)

2)Choose Test cases for Automation  
a)sanity test cases                - P1          P=(Priority)
b)data driven test cases/re-tests  - P2
c)Regression test cases            - P3
d)Any other test cases             - P4

3)Design & Development of framework
4)Execution - local,remote
5)Maintainance
         
 Project:E-commerce Domain (Domain:Insurance,Finance,Banking,Healthcare,Travel,E-commerce,Education,Telecom,Logistics)
 1)Frontend operations(customers/users) 	
  	- register an account
  	- login/logout
  	- search for the product
  	- add/edit/delete products from the cart
  	- order products
  	- reviews etc....
  2)Backend operations(admins/backend teams)
  	- products
  	- customers
  	- orders
  	- store etc....
  	
  ----------->https://tutorialsninja.com/demo/   (Opencart Application)
  
 --------------- Base Class contains all the common methods.-------------------
  
  Logging - record all the events in the form of text.
  Log Levels - All<Trace<Debug<Info<Warn<Error<Fatal<Off
  
  Appenders - where to generate logs(Console/File-preferred)
  Loggers - what type of logs to generate (All<Trace<Debug<Info<Warn<Error<Fatal<Off)
  
  